Want more development in your quadriceps or hamstrings? Then use this easy bodybuilding trick: Elevate your heels or toes during your next lower-body workout.

Raising your heels helps you sit deeper into your squat, which will recruit more muscle fibers and strengthen your quads. But the heels elevated squat is not an exercise for beginners. It is only to be performed by people who know how to squat properly. Practice without weight first and only when you’re comfortable with the exercise, use dumbbells or a barbell.

What’s on the agenda for today’s workout?

"Good morning" may be an email greeting, a cute text your boo sends while away on business, or, TBH, any morning that doesn't begin with an alarm clock. But "good morning" is also an exercise you should absolutely be doing.

Good Morning Squat is one of the best ways to build leg, hip and back strength. However, this exercise is often ignored out of fear of suffering a back injury. 

Never heard of it? This video is for you. Check out this training tip of our Dragon Pharma Athlete & Coach Kayla Rossi of how to perform Good Morning Squats to get the best results!

Full shoulder workout : 5 supersets , do 3 sets of 15 reps for each exercise in every superset . 
1. Bradford press (alternating front and back press) SUPERSET with triangle front raises 
2. Kneeling military press SUPERSET with seated lateral raises 
3. Around the worlds on preacher curl set up SUPERSET with reverse grip barbell front raises 
4. Forward leaning dumbbell presses (press out at an angle and pinch shoulder blades together) SUPERSET with reverse grip dumbbell presses 
5. Tick lateral raises (quarter , half, full is one rep) SUPERSET with upright rows 
*** FINISHER : plank step ups SUPERSET with kettle bell swings
#bouldershoulders#delts#shoulderworkout
